    Welcome from Mayor Byron W. Brown

    Thank you for stopping by Open Data Buffalo, the City's official open data portal. Stick around and explore the City through the data we generate every single day.

    Read the Mayor's Welcome
  • Featured Story Image 2

    Apply to Data 101

    Click here to learn more about Data 101, the City of Buffalo's data course, geared toward people like you to help you learn about open data, data visualization, and data analysis!

    Apply by November 1st!
  • Featured Story Image 3

    My Neighborhood Buffalo

    My Neighborhood Buffalo provides Buffalo residents with up-to-date, neighborhood-based information on crime and 311 service requests on one interactive map. Create an account to save searches and receive email alerts on new incidents.

    Explore your neighborhood
  • Featured Story Image 4

    City of Buffalo Open Data Policy

    Mayor Brown's Administration crafted a policy to govern and guide the open data program as it becomes an integral part of City government.

    Read the City's open data policy
